import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['open'] = pd.to_numeric(data['open'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['open'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['open'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['open'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['open'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['open'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of opening prices?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['close'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of closing prices over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Closing Price')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['volume'], data['close'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Volume')
    ax.set_ylabel('Closing Price')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between volume and closing prices?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['difference'] = data['high'] - data['low']
    plt.hist(data['difference'], bins=50, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['difference'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['difference'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['difference'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['difference'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of the difference between high and low prices?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['adjclose'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['adjclose'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['adjclose'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['adjclose'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['adjclose'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of adjusted closing prices?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
